Suggests: tor
Description: Secure Nostr identity management and signing service
 GNostr Signer is a GTK4/libadwaita application for managing Nostr identities
 and signing events. It keeps your private keys safe while allowing Nostr
 clients to request signatures through a secure D-Bus interface.
 .
 Features include:
  * Secure key storage using the system keyring (GNOME Keyring/libsecret)
  * Granular permission control for each application
  * Interactive approval dialogs for signing requests
  * NIP-46 remote signer (bunker) support
  * Multiple identity management with profiles
  * Backup and recovery options
  * Audit logging of signing operations
 .
 GNostr Signer implements NIP-55 (Signer Application) for local signing
 and NIP-46 (Nostr Connect) for remote signing capabilities.

Package: gnostr-signer-daemon
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         libglib2.0-0,
         libjson-glib-1.0-0,
         libsecret-1-0,
         dbus-user-session
Recommends: gnostr-signer
Description: GNostr Signer D-Bus daemon for Nostr signing operations
 The GNostr Signer daemon provides D-Bus and Unix socket interfaces for
 Nostr signing operations. It handles cryptographic operations without
 exposing private keys to client applications.
 .
 This package is typically used alongside gnostr-signer for headless
 operation or as a background service activated via D-Bus.
